<div class="container-fluid text center bg-1">
  <div class="jumbotron">
    <center><h1>Preconceito Racial</h1></center>  
  </div>
 <p> <h4> Black racist, hard to believe right?</h4></p>
 <p> But they do exist, and the worst, <b> we create them. </b> </p>
 
<P> We have created a racist every time we tell a child that his hair is bad for the simple fact that he is not smooth, we create a racist when we associate crime directly with black skin, we create a racist when we say that a poorly done service is "Black service," what we can expect from a person who grew up listening to these phrases but the reproduction of them, but the defamation of the race itself and the spread of hatred.

<P> Unfortunately, we have little hope, but there is still a solution, we can not change the past, but we can write our future, we can make the world a better place, without any kind of prejudice, but for that we must start by changing ourselves Same, we are all the same and it makes no sense to lower someone by their color, their hair or their place of origin. After all there is no good or bad hair, color does not define the character of someone, let alone their competence, so there is no place for prejudice </ p>
     
<center><img src="https://thatsatruestory.files.wordpress.com/2015/07/black_lives_hand_up_littlejohn_in_our_times.jpg" class= "img-responsive"></center>
   

            
       
